06/06/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A 16-year-old Serb boy was killed in a drive-by shooting in Gracanica on Saturday (5 June). A UN police spokesman said two ethnic Albanians have been arrested. They are suspected of having carried out the murder to provoke a new round of violence in the province. President Ibrahim Rugova and Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi quickly condemned the killing.
In other news, French KFOR troops found five Kosovo Albanians hiding in two trucks that were about to be loaded aboard ships in the Greek port of Thessaloniki. The stowaways said they had boarded the trucks in Skopje. (FoNET, B52, Tanjug - 05/06/04; Reuters, AFP - 04/06/04)
